    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.2",
          "pli": "“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa: ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.3",
          "pli": "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassatī”ti? ",
          "en": "does someone regard things like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.4",
          "pli": "Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … ",
          "en": "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.5",
          "pli": "“rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa … pe … ",
          "en": "“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.6",
          "pli": "viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa: ",
          "en": "When consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.7",
          "pli": "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati. ",
          "en": "someone regards it like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.8",
          "pli": "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, ",
          "en": "What do you think, mendicants? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.9",
          "pli": "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? ",
          "en": "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.10",
          "pli": "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … ",
          "en": "“Impermanent, sir.” … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.11",
          "pli": "vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attāti samanupasseyyāti? ",
          "en": "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would you regard it like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.12",
          "pli": "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. ",
          "en": "“No, sir.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.13",
          "pli": "“Vedanā … ",
          "en": "“Is feeling … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.14",
          "pli": "saññā … ",
          "en": "perception … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.15",
          "pli": "saṅkhārā … ",
          "en": "choices … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.16",
          "pli": "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? ",
          "en": "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.17",
          "pli": "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … ",
          "en": "“Impermanent, sir.” … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.18",
          "pli": "vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attāti samanupasseyyāti? ",
          "en": "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would you regard it like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.19",
          "pli": "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. ",
          "en": "“No, sir.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.20",
          "pli": "“Evaṃ passaṃ … pe … ",
          "en": "“Seeing this … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.21",
          "pli": "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti. ",
          "en": "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn22.151:1.22",
          "pli": "Dutiyaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
